""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
"                 General Settings
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
let mapleader=" "
let maplocalleader="-"

""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
"                 Custom Mappings
""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""

" Turn off search highlights by pressing return
nnoremap <cr> :noh<cr>

" Escape is too much of a reach. Use jk to exit insert mode
inoremap jk <esc>
" Also c-k works well for this
inoremap <c-k> <esc>

" Add a 'stamp' command to replace word or selection with yanked text
nnoremap S diw"0P
vnoremap S "_d"0P

" Make "Y" work from the cursor to end of line instead of like "yy"
nnoremap Y y$

" Reselect visual selection after indent
xnoremap < <gv
xnoremap > >gv

" These create newlines like o and O but stay in normal mode
nnoremap <silent> zj o<Esc>k
nnoremap <silent> zk O<Esc>j

" Also center the screen when jumping through the changelist
nnoremap g; g;zz
nnoremap g, g,zz

" Use Q for formatting the current paragraph (or visual selection)
vnoremap Q gq
nnoremap Q gqap

" This makes j and k work on "screen lines" instead of on "file lines"
" Still allows situations like 5j to move 5 real lines instead of screen lines"
nnoremap <expr> j (v:count == 0 ? 'gj' : 'j')
nnoremap <expr> k (v:count == 0 ? 'gk' : 'k')

" Swap implementations of ` and ' jump to markers
nnoremap ' `
nnoremap ` '

" Quick navigation to start/end of line
nnoremap E $
nnoremap B ^
vnoremap E $
vnoremap B ^

" Move between editors (tabs) faster
nnoremap <C-n> gt
nnoremap <C-b> gT

" Switch to most recent editor
nnoremap <leader><leader> <C-^>

" Comment toggle (if using VSCodeVim commentary)
xmap gc <Plug>VSCodeCommentary
nmap gc <Plug>VSCodeCommentary
omap gc <Plug>VSCodeCommentary
nmap gcc <Plug>VSCodeCommentaryLine
